In your HTML document (index.html), within the <head> section (usually located between the <head> and </head> tags), 
add the following line:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

<link>: This is an HTML element used to link external resources to your HTML document.

rel="stylesheet": This attribute specifies the relationship between the HTML document and the linked resource. 
In this case, it indicates that you are linking a stylesheet.

type="text/css": This attribute specifies the type of the linked resource. In this case, it's a CSS file, so it's set to "text/css."

href="styles.css": This attribute specifies the path to the CSS file you want to link to. 
Make sure to replace "styles.css" with the actual filename and path to your CSS file.

The title attribute is used for providing additional information about the element when a user hovers their mouse pointer over it.

